-- Nordic Stocks: Acergy, FLSmidth, Ratos, Skanska, TGS Shares Are Active
-- B y   A d a m   E w i n g   a n d   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2010-11-04T10:14:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/nordic-stocks-acergy-flsmidth-ratos-skanska-tgs-shares-are-active.html
The  Stoxx Nordic 30 Index , the
benchmark measure for the region, jumped 1.7 percent to 7,072.36
at 11:01 a.m., the highest since Oct. 25.  The  OMX Stockholm 30 Index  climbed 1.9 percent, while
Norway’s  OBX Index  advanced 1.5 percent. The  OMX Helsinki 25
Index  rose 1.8 percent and Denmark’s  Copenhagen 20 Index  added
1.2 percent.  The following companies’ shares were among the most active
in Nordic markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  Acergy SA  (ACY NO) increased 2 percent to 130.1 kroner, up
13 percent since Oct. 27. The U.K. provider of oil services won
a contract worth $50 million in the North Sea.  FLSmidth & Co. A/S  (FLS DC) rose 4.1 percent to 414.7
kroner, the biggest gain since Sept. 1. The world’s largest
maker of cement kilns rose after its customer HeidelbergCement
AG said demand is picking up and that its third-quarter profit
more than doubled. Separately, FLSmidth said its mining
equipment unit won a $40 million contract in Mauritania.  Ratos AB  (RATOB SS) climbed 1.6 percent to 240 kronor,
erasing yesterday’s 1.3 percent slide. The Swedish investment
company said third-quarter net income rose to 1.23 billion
kronor from 276 million kronor a year earlier.  Skanska AB  (SKAB SS) jumped 3.7 percent to 129.6 kronor,
the biggest gain in two months. Sweden’s biggest builder said
third-quarter net income was 1.20 billion kronor. Analysts had
estimated net income of 1.09 billion kronor, according to a
survey compiled by Bloomberg.  TGS Nopec Geophysical Company ASA  (TGS NO) climbed 7.6
percent to 115 kroner. The Norwegian oil and gas service
provider reported third-quarter net income of $37.9 million,
surpassing analysts’ average estimate of $33.4 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
